modules.description: This module creates a session manager that uses Lwt for asynchronous operations with Cohttp, providing functions to retrieve, create, update, and delete sessions using a customizable backend. It works with string-based keys and values, and expiration periods in seconds, tracking modifications to control cookie header generation. Concrete use cases include managing user sessions in web applications by extracting session keys from HTTP headers, creating new sessions with default or custom expiration, and updating or clearing session data in the backend.

This module implements an asynchronous session manager for Cohttp using Lwt, enabling session management with string-based keys and values, and configurable expiration times in seconds. It supports retrieving, creating, updating, and deleting sessions, with tracking of modifications to control cookie header generation. The module integrates with Cohttp by extracting session keys from HTTP headers and allows interaction with various backends for session storage. Example usage includes managing user authentication sessions in web applications, setting custom expiration times, and updating session data dynamically during requests.
